    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I attempted the naive solution of moving the Plugin Loader until after config was initialized, but that resulted in running `Nethermind.Config.ConfigProvider.Initialize()` a second time because the plugin DLL will be loaded *after* Initialize was run the first time, which means when it goes looking to see if the config is already loaded it finds not, so it assumes it needs to initialize everything.\r\n\r\nOn top of that, it appears that `TypeDiscovery` would need to be re-initialized after the plugins are loaded as well.\r\n\r\nShort term remediation: Remove `PluginsDirectory` configuration option and regenerate docs so users aren't confused.\r\nLong term remediation: Rearchitect things so plugins can be loaded *after* config initialization so the plugin directory can be configured.",
